msgid "So ācariyassa ācariyadhanaṃ niyyādetvā dāraṃ pariyesati dhammeneva, no adhammena. "
msgstr "Having offered the fee to his teacher, he seeks a wife, but only by legitimate means, not illegitimate. "

#. HTML: </p><p>
#. REF: pts-vp-pli3.227, sc8
msgctxt "an5.192:8.1"
msgid "Tattha ca, doṇa, ko dhammo? "
msgstr "In this context, Doṇa, what is legitimate? "

msgctxt "an5.192:8.2"
msgid "Neva kayena na vikkayena, brāhmaṇiṃyeva udakūpassaṭṭhaṃ. "
msgstr "Not by buying or selling, he only accepts a brahmin woman by the pouring of water. "

# NOTE: see https://discourse.suttacentral.net/t/menstruation-and-fertility-in-the-pali-texts/3042
#. VAR: na veniṃ → na veṇiṃ (bj, s1-3, km, pts1)
msgctxt "an5.192:8.3"
msgid "So brāhmaṇiṃyeva gacchati, na khattiyiṃ na vessiṃ na suddiṃ na caṇḍāliṃ na nesādiṃ na veniṃ na rathakāriṃ na pukkusiṃ gacchati, na gabbhiniṃ gacchati, na pāyamānaṃ gacchati, na anutuniṃ gacchati. "
msgstr "He has sex only with a brahmin woman. He does not have sex with a woman from a caste of aristocrats, merchants, workers, outcastes, hunters, bamboo workers, chariot-makers, or waste-collectors. Nor does he have sex with women who are pregnant, breastfeeding, or outside the fertile half of the month that starts with menstruation. "

#. HTML: </p><p>
msgctxt "an5.192:8.4"
msgid "Kasmā ca, doṇa, brāhmaṇo na gabbhiniṃ gacchati? "
msgstr "And why does the brahmin not have sex with a pregnant woman? "

#. VAR: māṇavikā → māṇavakī (mr)
msgctxt "an5.192:8.5"
msgid "Sace, doṇa, brāhmaṇo gabbhiniṃ gacchati, atimīḷhajo nāma so hoti māṇavako vā māṇavikā vā. "
msgstr "If a brahmin had sex with a pregnant woman, the boy or girl would be born in too much filth. "

msgctxt "an5.192:8.6"
msgid "Tasmā, doṇa, brāhmaṇo na gabbhiniṃ gacchati. "
msgstr "That’s why the brahmin doesn’t have sex with a pregnant woman. "

#. HTML: </p><p>
msgctxt "an5.192:8.7"
msgid "Kasmā ca, doṇa, brāhmaṇo na pāyamānaṃ gacchati? "
msgstr "And why does the brahmin not have sex with a breastfeeding woman? "

# NOTE: See BB’s note. I adopt his reading, however note that here, as often, asuci means “semen”. It’s important to clarify this, as the “foulness” of the body is too often associated with women only.
msgctxt "an5.192:8.8"
msgid "Sace, doṇa, brāhmaṇo pāyamānaṃ gacchati, asucipaṭipīḷito nāma so hoti māṇavako vā māṇavikā vā. "
msgstr "If a brahmin had sex with a breastfeeding woman, the boy or girl would drink back the semen. "

msgctxt "an5.192:8.9"
msgid "Tasmā, doṇa, brāhmaṇo na pāyamānaṃ gacchati. "
msgstr "That’s why the brahmin doesn’t have sex with a breastfeeding woman. "

#. HTML: </p><p>
# NOTE: See BB on variant readings here. It seems the question has been lost and the text corrupted.
msgctxt "an5.192:8.10"
msgid "Tassa sā hoti brāhmaṇī neva kāmatthā na davatthā na ratatthā, pajatthāva brāhmaṇassa brāhmaṇī hoti. "
msgstr "And why does the brahmin not have sex outside the fertile half of the month that starts with menstruation? Because his brahmin wife is not there for sensual pleasure, fun, and enjoyment, but only for procreation. "

# NOTE: Comm: Methunaṃuppādetvāti dhītaraṃ vā puttaṃ vā uppādetvā ‘‘idāni paveṇi ghaṭīyissatī’’ti nikkhamitvā pabbajati
msgctxt "an5.192:8.11"
msgid "So methunaṃ uppādetvā kesamassuṃ ohāretvā kāsāyāni vatthāni acchādetvā agārasmā anagāriyaṃ pabbajati. "
msgstr "Having ensured his progeny through sex, he shaves off his hair and beard, dresses in ocher robes, and goes forth from the lay life to homelessness. "

#. HTML: </p><p>
msgctxt "an5.192:8.12"
msgid "So evaṃ pabbajito samāno vivicceva kāmehi … pe … catutthaṃ jhānaṃ upasampajja viharati. "
msgstr "When he has gone forth, quite secluded from sensual pleasures, secluded from unskillful qualities, he enters and remains in the first absorption … second absorption … third absorption … fourth absorption. "

# NOTE: Notice the jhanas lead to heaven, not Brahma realms.
msgctxt "an5.192:8.13"
msgid "So ime cattāro jhāne bhāvetvā kāyassa bhedā paraṃ maraṇā sugatiṃ saggaṃ lokaṃ upapajjati. "
msgstr "Having developed these four absorptions, when the body breaks up, after death, they’re reborn in a good place, a heavenly realm. "

#. HTML: </p><p>
msgctxt "an5.192:8.14"
msgid "Evaṃ kho, doṇa, brāhmaṇo devasamo hoti. (2) "
msgstr "That’s how a brahmin is equal to god. "

#. HTML: </p><p>
#. REF: sc9
