msgstr " "

msgctxt "an5.192:10.5"
msgid "Sace, doṇa, brāhmaṇo gabbhiniṃ gacchati, atimīḷhajo nāma so hoti māṇavako vā māṇavikā vā. "
msgstr " "

msgctxt "an5.192:10.6"
msgid "Tasmā, doṇa, brāhmaṇo na gabbhiniṃ gacchati. "
msgstr " "

msgctxt "an5.192:10.7"
msgid "Kasmā ca, doṇa, brāhmaṇo na pāyamānaṃ gacchati? "
msgstr " "

msgctxt "an5.192:10.8"
msgid "Sace, doṇa, brāhmaṇo pāyamānaṃ gacchati, asucipaṭipīḷito nāma so hoti māṇavako vā māṇavikā vā. "
msgstr " "

msgctxt "an5.192:10.9"
msgid "Tasmā, doṇa, brāhmaṇo na pāyamānaṃ gacchati. "
msgstr " "

msgctxt "an5.192:10.10"
msgid "Tassa sā hoti brāhmaṇī neva kāmatthā na davatthā na ratatthā, pajatthāva brāhmaṇassa brāhmaṇī hoti. "
msgstr " "

msgctxt "an5.192:10.11"
msgid "So methunaṃ uppādetvā tameva puttassādaṃ nikāmayamāno kuṭumbaṃ ajjhāvasati, na agārasmā anagāriyaṃ pabbajati. "
msgstr "Having ensured his progeny through sex, his child makes him happy. Because of this attachment he stays in his family property, and does not go forth from the lay life to homelessness. "

#. HTML: </p><p>
msgctxt "an5.192:10.12"
msgid "Yāva porāṇānaṃ brāhmaṇānaṃ mariyādo tattha tiṭṭhati, taṃ na vītikkamati. "
msgstr "As far as the line of the ancient brahmins extends, he doesn’t cross over it. "

msgctxt "an5.192:10.13"
msgid "‘Yāva porāṇānaṃ brāhmaṇānaṃ mariyādo tattha brāhmaṇo ṭhito taṃ na vītikkamatī’ti, kho, doṇa, tasmā brāhmaṇo mariyādoti vuccati. "
msgstr "That’s why he’s called a brahmin who toes the line. "

#. HTML: </p><p>
msgctxt "an5.192:10.14"
msgid "Evaṃ kho, doṇa, brāhmaṇo mariyādo hoti. (3) "
msgstr "That’s how a brahmin toes the line. "

#. HTML: </p><p>
#. REF: pts-vp-pli3.228, sc11
msgctxt "an5.192:11.1"
msgid "Kathañca, doṇa, brāhmaṇo sambhinnamariyādo hoti? "
msgstr "And how does a brahmin cross the line? "

#. HTML: </p><p>
msgctxt "an5.192:11.2"
msgid "Idha, doṇa, brāhmaṇo ubhato sujāto hoti—"
msgstr "It’s when a brahmin is well born on both the mother’s and the father’s sides … "

msgctxt "an5.192:11.3"
msgid "mātito ca pitito ca, saṃsuddhagahaṇiko, yāva sattamā pitāmahayugā akkhitto anupakkuṭṭho jātivādena. "
msgstr " "

msgctxt "an5.192:11.4"
msgid "So aṭṭhacattālīsavassāni komārabrahmacariyaṃ carati mante adhīyamāno. "
msgstr " "

msgctxt "an5.192:11.5"
msgid "Aṭṭhacattālīsavassāni komārabrahmacariyaṃ caritvā mante adhīyitvā ācariyassa ācariyadhanaṃ pariyesati dhammeneva, no adhammena. "
msgstr " "

#. HTML: </p><p>
#. REF: sc12
msgctxt "an5.192:12.1"
msgid "Tattha ca, doṇa, ko dhammo? "
msgstr " "

msgctxt "an5.192:12.2"
msgid "Neva kasiyā na vaṇijjāya na gorakkhena na issatthena na rājaporisena na sippaññatarena, kevalaṃ bhikkhācariyāya kapālaṃ anatimaññamāno. "
msgstr " "

msgctxt "an5.192:12.3"
msgid "So ācariyassa ācariyadhanaṃ niyyādetvā dāraṃ pariyesati dhammenapi adhammenapi kayenapi vikkayenapi brāhmaṇimpi udakūpassaṭṭhaṃ. "
msgstr "Having offered a fee for his teacher, he seeks a wife by both legitimate and illegitimate means. That is, by buying or selling, as well as accepting a brahmin woman by the pouring of water. "

msgctxt "an5.192:12.4"
msgid "So brāhmaṇimpi gacchati khattiyimpi gacchati vessimpi gacchati suddimpi gacchati caṇḍālimpi gacchati nesādimpi gacchati venimpi gacchati rathakārimpi gacchati pukkusimpi gacchati gabbhinimpi gacchati pāyamānampi gacchati utunimpi gacchati anutunimpi gacchati. "
msgstr "He has sex with a brahmin woman, as well as with a woman from a caste of aristocrats, merchants, workers, outcastes, hunters, bamboo workers, chariot-makers, or waste-collectors. And he has sex with women who are pregnant, breastfeeding, or outside the fertile half of the month that starts with menstruation. "

msgctxt "an5.192:12.5"
msgid "Tassa sā hoti brāhmaṇī kāmatthāpi davatthāpi ratatthāpi pajatthāpi brāhmaṇassa brāhmaṇī hoti. "
msgstr "His brahmin wife is there for sensual pleasure, fun, and enjoyment, as well as for procreation. "

#. HTML: </p><p>
msgctxt "an5.192:12.6"
msgid "Yāva porāṇānaṃ brāhmaṇānaṃ mariyādo tattha na tiṭṭhati, taṃ vītikkamati. "
msgstr "As far as the line of the ancient brahmins extends, he crosses over it. "

msgctxt "an5.192:12.7"
msgid "‘Yāva porāṇānaṃ brāhmaṇānaṃ mariyādo tattha brāhmaṇo na ṭhito taṃ vītikkamatī’ti kho, doṇa, tasmā brāhmaṇo sambhinnamariyādoti vuccati. "
msgstr "That’s why he’s called a brahmin who crosses the line. "

#. HTML: </p><p>
msgctxt "an5.192:12.8"
msgid "Evaṃ kho, doṇa, brāhmaṇo sambhinnamariyādo hoti. (4) "
msgstr "That’s how a brahmin crosses the line. "

#. HTML: </p><p>
#. REF: pts-vp-pli3.229, sc13
msgctxt "an5.192:13.1"
msgid "Kathañca, doṇa, brāhmaṇo brāhmaṇacaṇḍālo hoti? "
msgstr "And how is a brahmin a brahmin outcaste? "

#. HTML: </p><p>
msgctxt "an5.192:13.2"
msgid "Idha, doṇa, brāhmaṇo ubhato sujāto hoti—"
msgstr "It’s when a brahmin is well born on both the mother’s and the father’s sides, coming from a clean womb back to the seventh paternal generation, incontestable and irreproachable in discussions about ancestry. "

msgctxt "an5.192:13.3"
msgid "mātito ca pitito ca, saṃsuddhagahaṇiko, yāva sattamā pitāmahayugā akkhitto anupakkuṭṭho jātivādena. "
msgstr " "

msgctxt "an5.192:13.4"
msgid "So aṭṭhacattālīsavassāni komārabrahmacariyaṃ carati mante adhīyamāno. "
msgstr "For forty-eight years he lives the spiritual life, from childhood, studying the hymns. "

# NOTE: See BB’s note.
msgctxt "an5.192:13.5"
msgid "Aṭṭhacattālīsavassāni komārabrahmacariyaṃ caritvā mante adhīyitvā ācariyassa ācariyadhanaṃ pariyesati dhammenapi adhammenapi "
msgstr "Then he seeks a fee for his teacher by legitimate means and illegitimate means. "

msgctxt "an5.192:13.6"
msgid "kasiyāpi vaṇijjāyapi gorakkhenapi issatthenapi rājaporisenapi sippaññatarenapi, kevalampi bhikkhācariyāya, kapālaṃ anatimaññamāno. "
msgstr "By farming, trade, raising cattle, archery, government service, or one of the professions, not solely by living on alms, not scorning the alms bowl. "

#. HTML: </p><p>
#. REF: sc14
msgctxt "an5.192:14.1"
msgid "So ācariyassa ācariyadhanaṃ niyyādetvā dāraṃ pariyesati dhammenapi adhammenapi kayenapi vikkayenapi brāhmaṇimpi udakūpassaṭṭhaṃ. "
msgstr "Having offered a fee for his teacher, he seeks a wife by both legitimate and illegitimate means. That is, by buying or selling, as well as accepting a brahmin woman by the pouring of water. "

msgctxt "an5.192:14.2"
msgid "So brāhmaṇimpi gacchati khattiyimpi gacchati vessimpi gacchati suddimpi gacchati caṇḍālimpi gacchati nesādimpi gacchati venimpi gacchati rathakārimpi gacchati pukkusimpi gacchati gabbhinimpi gacchati pāyamānampi gacchati utunimpi gacchati anutunimpi gacchati. "
msgstr "He has sex with a brahmin woman, as well as with a woman from a caste of aristocrats, merchants, workers, outcastes, hunters, bamboo workers, chariot-makers, or waste-collectors. And he has sex with women who are pregnant, breastfeeding, or outside the fertile half of the month that starts with menstruation. "

msgctxt "an5.192:14.3"
msgid "Tassa sā hoti brāhmaṇī kāmatthāpi davatthāpi ratatthāpi pajatthāpi brāhmaṇassa brāhmaṇī hoti. "
msgstr "His brahmin wife is there for sensual pleasure, fun, and enjoyment, as well as for procreation. "

#. HTML: </p><p>
#. VAR: jīvikaṃ → jīvitaṃ (s1-3, mr)
msgctxt "an5.192:14.4"
msgid "So sabbakammehi jīvikaṃ kappeti. "
msgstr "He earns a living by any kind of work. "

msgctxt "an5.192:14.5"
msgid "Tamenaṃ brāhmaṇā evamāhaṃsu: "
msgstr "The brahmins say to him, "

msgctxt "an5.192:14.6"
msgid "‘kasmā bhavaṃ brāhmaṇo paṭijānamāno sabbakammehi jīvikaṃ kappetī’ti? "
msgstr "‘My good man, why is it that you claim to be a brahmin, but you earn a living by any kind of work?’ "

#. HTML: </p><p>
msgctxt "an5.192:14.7"
msgid "So evamāha: "
msgstr "He says, "

#. VAR: upalippati → upalimpati (mr)
msgctxt "an5.192:14.8"
msgid "‘seyyathāpi, bho, aggi sucimpi ḍahati asucimpi ḍahati, na ca tena aggi upalippati; "
msgstr "‘It’s like a fire that burns both pure and filthy substances, but doesn’t become corrupted by them. "

msgctxt "an5.192:14.9"
msgid "evamevaṃ kho, bho, sabbakammehi cepi brāhmaṇo jīvikaṃ kappeti, na ca tena brāhmaṇo upalippati. "
msgstr "In the same way, my good man, if a brahmin earns a living by any kind of work, he is not corrupted by that.’ "

#. HTML: </p><p>
msgctxt "an5.192:14.10"
msgid "Sabbakammehi jīvikaṃ kappetī’ti kho, doṇa, tasmā brāhmaṇo brāhmaṇacaṇḍāloti vuccati. "
msgstr "A brahmin is called a brahmin outcaste because he earns a living by any kind of work. "

#. HTML: </p><p>
msgctxt "an5.192:14.11"
msgid "Evaṃ kho, doṇa, brāhmaṇo brāhmaṇacaṇḍālo hoti. "
msgstr "That’s how a brahmin is a brahmin outcaste. "

#. HTML: </p><p>
#. REF: pts-vp-pli3.230, sc15
msgctxt "an5.192:15.1"
msgid "Ye kho te, doṇa, brāhmaṇānaṃ pubbakā isayo mantānaṃ kattāro mantānaṃ pavattāro yesamidaṃ etarahi brāhmaṇā porāṇaṃ mantapadaṃ gītaṃ pavuttaṃ samīhitaṃ tadanugāyanti tadanubhāsanti bhāsitamanubhāsanti sajjhāyitamanusajjhāyanti vācitamanuvācenti, seyyathidaṃ—aṭṭhako, vāmako, vāmadevo, vessāmitto, yamadaggi, aṅgīraso, bhāradvājo, vāseṭṭho, kassapo, bhagu; "
msgstr "Doṇa, the brahmin hermits of the past were Aṭṭhaka, Vāmaka, Vāmadeva, Vessāmitta, Yamadaggi, Aṅgīrasa, Bhāradvāja, Vāseṭṭha, Kassapa, and Bhagu. They were the authors and propagators of the hymns, whose hymnal was sung and propagated and compiled in ancient times. These days, brahmins continue to sing and chant it. They continue chanting what was chanted, reciting what was recited, and teaching what was taught. "

#. HTML: </p><p>
msgctxt "an5.192:15.2"
msgid "tyassume pañca brāhmaṇe paññāpenti—"
msgstr "Those hermits described five kinds of brahmins. "

msgctxt "an5.192:15.3"
msgid "brahmasamaṃ, devasamaṃ, mariyādaṃ, sambhinnamariyādaṃ, brāhmaṇacaṇḍālaṃyeva pañcamaṃ. "
msgstr "A brahmin who is equal to Brahmā, one who is equal to a god, one who toes the line, one who crosses the line, and the fifth is a brahmin outcaste. "

msgctxt "an5.192:15.4"
msgid "Tesaṃ tvaṃ, doṇa, katamoti? "
msgstr "Which one of these are you, Doṇa?” "

#. HTML: </p><p>
#. REF: sc16
msgctxt "an5.192:16.1"
msgid "Evaṃ sante mayaṃ, bho gotama, brāhmaṇacaṇḍālampi na pūrema. "
msgstr "“This being so, Master Gotama, I don’t even qualify as a brahmin outcaste. "

#. HTML: </p><p>
msgctxt "an5.192:16.2"
msgid "Abhikkantaṃ, bho gotama … pe … upāsakaṃ maṃ bhavaṃ gotamo dhāretu ajjatagge pāṇupetaṃ saraṇaṃ gatan”ti. "
msgstr "Excellent, Master Gotama! … From this day forth, may Master Gotama remember me as a lay follower who has gone for refuge for life.” "

#. HTML: </p><p class="endsection">
msgctxt "an5.192:16.3"
msgid "Dutiyaṃ. "
msgstr ""

